{"error":"Parsing failed","timestamp":"2026-04-20T17:06:48.3297366Z","source":"enbridge","pipeline":"AG","noticeId":"176682","rawBlobPath":"raw/enbridge/2026-04-18/AG/176682.html","errorDetails":"[{\"name\":\"Get_HTML_Blob_Content\",\"inputs\":{\"uri\":\"https://stdtenoticeappeus2mx01.blob.core.windows.net/critical-notices/raw/enbridge/2026-04-18/AG/176682.html\",\"method\":\"GET\",\"headers\":{\"x-ms-version\":\"2020-10-02\"},\"authentication\":{\"audience\":\"https://storage.azure.com/\",\"type\":\"ManagedServiceIdentity\"}},\"outputs\":{\"statusCode\":200,\"headers\":{\"Accept-Ranges\":\"bytes\",\"ETag\":\"\\\"0x8DE9D607DD233F4\\\"\",\"Server\":\"Windows-Azure-Blob/1.0,Microsoft-HTTPAPI/2.0\",\"x-ms-request-id\":\"5f5c9e17-b01e-0072-60e8-d095af000000\",\"x-ms-client-request-id\":\"50a9e69b-2441-4c3b-b06e-94fac6884a32\",\"x-ms-version\":\"2020-10-02\",\"x-ms-tag-count\":\"2\",\"x-ms-creation-time\":\"Sat, 18 Apr 2026 15:38:08 GMT\",\"x-ms-lease-status\":\"unlocked\",\"x-ms-lease-state\":\"available\",\"x-ms-blob-type\":\"BlockBlob\",\"x-ms-server-encrypted\":\"true\",\"x-ms-access-tier\":\"Hot\",\"x-ms-access-tier-inferred\":\"true\",\"Date\":\"Mon, 20 Apr 2026 17:06:47 GMT\",\"Content-Length\":\"17060\",\"Content-Type\":\"text/html\",\"Content-MD5\":\"2mIhPJGmjoScaw9QhsXWZw==\",\"Last-Modified\":\"Sat, 18 Apr 2026 15:38:08 GMT\"},\"body\":\"<!-- template.asp -->\\r\\n<html><head><title>Algonquin Gas Transmission, LLC 006951446 : Critical Notices</title><link rel=stylesheet href='/styles/infopost.css' type='text/css'><link rel=stylesheet href='NoticeDetail.css' type='text/css'></head><body><div id=main><script type='text/javascript'> function Print() {if (document.queryCommandSupported('print')) {document.execCommand('print', false, null);\\t}else {window.parent.print(); }}</script><div class=recordsetBar><a class=recordsetBar href='javascript:history.go(-1)'>Back</a><a class=recordsetBar href='#' onClick='Print();return false'>Print</a></div><div id=bulletinContents><div class=headingArea><div id=heading>TSP:&nbsp<br>TSP Name:&nbsp<br>Critical Notice Description:&nbsp<br>Notice Effective Date:&nbsp<br>Notice Effective Time:&nbsp<br>Notice End Date:&nbsp<br>Notice End Time:&nbsp<br>Notice Identifier:&nbsp<br>Notice Status Description:&nbsp<br>Notice Type:&nbsp<br>Posting Date:&nbsp<br>Posting Time:&nbsp<br>Prior Notice Identifier:&nbsp<br>Required Response<br>&nbsp; Indicator Description:&nbsp<br>Response Date:&nbsp<br>Response Time:&nbsp<br>Subject:&nbsp<br></div><div id=headingData>006951446<br>Algonquin Gas Transmission, LLC<br>Critical notice<br>04/20/2026<br>09:00:00 AM<br>04/22/2026<br>09:00:00 AM<br>176682<br>Initiate<br>Operational Flow Order<br>04/16/2026<br>03:05:00 PM<br> <br><br>No response required<br> <br> <br>AGT Operational Flow Order -- EFF 4/20<br></div></div><br><div id=bulletin><br><div id=heading>Notice Text:</div><br><p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><a>In order to maintain the operational integrity of the system, AGT is issuing an Operational Flow Order (OFO) pursuant to Section 26 of the General Terms and Conditions of AGT's FERC Gas Tariff effective 9:00 AM CCT, April 20, 2026, to all parties, with the exception of those Operational Balancing Agreements required by FERC regulations, on the AGT system.&nbsp; </a></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>This OFO does not affect the ability of AGT to receive or deliver quantities of gas for scheduled nominations to any customer or pipeline.</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><a>During the effectiveness of this OFO, all parties must be balanced such that actual deliveries of gas out of the system must be equal to or less than scheduled deliveries out of the system.&nbsp; The penalty shall apply to each dekatherm of actual delivery quantities that are greater than scheduled quantities plus 500 Dth or 105% of scheduled delivery quantities.</a>&nbsp; The penalty will be equal to three times the arithmetic average of daily Platts Gas Daily \\\"Daily Price Survey\\\" posting for the High Common price for \\\"Algonquin, city-gates\\\" for the day on which such violation occurred as indicated in AGT's General Terms and Conditions Section 26.8.&nbsp;&nbsp; In addition, AGT will not permit retroactive nominations from upstream interconnects governed by a FERC gas tariff to avoid an OFO penalty.</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>AGT may be required to issue system specific and/or hourly OFO<span style=\\\"color: rgb(31, 73, 125);\\\">'s</span> pursuant to General Terms and Conditions Section 26.7(d) to impose further restrictions in order to maintain the operational integrity of the system.</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>This OFO will remain in effect until 9:00 AM CCT, April 22, 2026.</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>Please contact your Operations Account Representative should you have any questions.</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span>Please refer to the table below for the effected AGT operational areas, dates, and tolerance percentages:</span></p> \\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><span style=\\\"font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\\\">&nbsp;</span></span></p> \\n<div> \\n <table border=\\\"1\\\" width=\\\"752\\\" style=\\\"width: 749px; border-collapse: collapse; border-width: medium; border-style: none; border-color: currentcolor; border-image: initial;\\\"> \\n  <tbody> \\n   <tr style=\\\"height: 60px;\\\"> \\n    <td width=\\\"126\\\" style=\\\"width: 125px; border: 1px solid windowtext; padding: 0in 7px; height: 60px;\\\"> <p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif;\\\"><span><b><span style=\\\"font-size: 15px;\\\">Operational Area</span></b></span></p> </td> \\n    <td width=\\\"125\\\" style=\\\"width: 125px; border-width: 1px 1px 1px medium; border-style: solid solid solid none; border-color: windowtext windowtext windowtext currentcolor; border-image: initial; padding: 0in 7px; height: 60px;\\\"> <p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; text-align: center;\\\"><span><b><span style=\\\"font-size: 15px;\\\">Gas Day April 16 </span></b></span></p> </td> \\n    <td width=\\\"125\\\" style=\\\"width: 125px; border-width: 1px 1px 1px medium; border-style: solid solid solid none; border-color: windowtext windowtext windowtext currentcolor; border-image: initial; padding: 0in 7px; height: 60px;\\\"> <p style=\\\"margin: 0in; font-size: 16px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; text-align: center;\\\"><span><b><span style=\\\"font-size: 15px;\\\">Gas Day April 17 </span></b></span></p> </td> \\n    <td width=\\\"125\\\" style=\\\"width: 125px; bord